This product contains phone-numbering metadata derived from libphonenumber
(https://github.com/google/libphonenumber), Copyright (c) The libphonenumber
Authors, licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Derived data was generated from the "phonenumbers" Python distribution,
version 9.0.34, and reduced to the fields used by this package. See
tool/gen_phone_metadata.py for the extraction process.

Austrian bank reference data (bank sort codes, names and BICs) is derived from
the SEPA payment directory published by the Oesterreichische Nationalbank
(OeNB), used under its terms. IBAN structure data is derived from the SWIFT IBAN
Registry as bundled by the schwifty project.

German bank reference data (bank sort codes, names and BICs) is derived from the
Bankleitzahlen directory published by the Deutsche Bundesbank. Swiss bank
reference data is derived from the SIX Bank Master published by SIX Interbank
Clearing. Both are used under their respective terms.

German license-plate region data (Unterscheidungszeichen and their assigned
Stadt/Kreis) is derived from the Kraftfahrt-Bundesamt's official list, an
amtliches Werk in the public domain under German copyright law. Other plate
region tables are compiled from public administrative sources.

Per-country postal-code patterns are derived from Google's libaddressinput
(https://github.com/google/libaddressinput) i18n address format data, used
under its Apache License, Version 2.0.
